Issue 508 : Cannot have access to cross-platform lanes ， Issue #508 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub I have set up some cross-platform (aka general) lanes  but I cannot call them. If I call fastlane general_lane I have this error: Could not find lane 'ios general_lane'. Available lanes: ios platform_lane  general_lane If I call fastlane it only prompts me for the ios lane: You must provide a lane to drive. Available lanes: 1) ios platform_lane  And the lane platform_lane can be called using fastlane platform_lane with no error. Here is the Fastfile used in the examples above fastlane_version "1.11.0"  default_platform :ios  platform :ios do    before_all do |lane|   end    desc "Do nothing"   lane :platform_lane do   end    after_all do |lane|     # This block is called  only if the executed lane was successful   end    error do |lane  exception|   end  end  desc "General lane." lane :general_lane do end

Issue 519 : Generated .ipa size too big ， Issue #519 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Using Xcode 7 Beta 5  Swift 2.0 and fastlane 1.19.0 our generated .ipa file size has increased from 9.8 MB to 60 MB. Picking the archive produced by fastlane in Xcode Organizer and exporting for enterprise deployment the target .ipa file has the expected size of 9.8 MB. After inspecting the small and big ipa it turns out that the big one has duplicated dylib files ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftCore.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftCoreAudio.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftCoreGraphics.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftCoreImage.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftDarwin.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftDispatch.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftFoundation.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftObjectiveC.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftSecurity.dylib ./Payload/Client.app/Frameworks/libswiftUIKit.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftCore.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftCoreAudio.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftCoreGraphics.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftCoreImage.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftDarwin.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftDispatch.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftFoundation.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftObjectiveC.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftSecurity.dylib ./SwiftSupport/libswiftUIKit.dylib  (this is taken from here: http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30602808/how-to-prevent-swiftsupport-libraries-to-be-included-twice) From the fastlane log: [14:51:45]: Successfully stored the archive. You can find it in the Xcode Organizer. [14:51:45]: /usr/bin/xcrun /tmp/PackageApplication4Gym -v '/Users/orschaef/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives/2015-08-20/example 2015-08-20 14.49.32.xcarchive/Products/Applications/example.app' -o '/Users/orschaef/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives/2015-08-20/example.ipa' exportFormat ipa --embed 'example.mobileprovision'  [14:51:50]: zip --recurse-paths /Users/orschaef/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives/2015-08-20/example.ipa SwiftSupport > /dev/null [14:51:53]: cd '/Users/orschaef/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives/2015-08-20/example 2015-08-20 14.49.32.xcarchive/dSYMs' && zip -r '/Users/orschaef/workspace/example/example.app.dSYM.zip' 'example.app.dSYM'  Could the following line  ... SwiftSupport > /dev/null ...  be part of the problem? This does not seem to be a fastlane only problem (but for us it does only appear in combination with fastlane). Maybe we can find the solution and also update the docs like @KrauseFx did for KrauseFx#258

Issue 1039 : Git Last Tag on a shallow clone ， Issue #1039 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub I have a question about working with the git_last_tag command on a shallow clone. I'm using bamboo as my CI server and fastlane. Bamboo (by default) does a shallow clone which doesn't seem to be pulling tags correctly. I follow that up with a git fetch --tags which then pulls in the tags. I've noticed in git_helper.rb it looks like the last_tag command is doing git describe --tags --abbrev=0 def self.last_git_tag_name(match_lightweight = true)   command = ['git describe']   command << '--tags' if match_lightweight   command << '--abbrev=0'   Actions.sh(command.join(' ')  log: false).chomp  rescue   nil  end  This doesn't seem to be working correctly whereas the command: git describe --tags `git rev-list --tags --max-count=1`  does pull the last tag correctly. Should the code be updated to mirror this behavior? I guess i'm a little clear what "last_tag" means.

Issue 1422 : set_info_plist_value changes Info.plist XML header to "... Apple Computer"; PlistBuddy changes it to "Apple" = diff annoyance ， Issue #1422 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub I use the GIT_COMMIT_COUNT trick for build numbers powered by PlistBuddy in the Xcode build phases normally. But I found the version doesn't stick around if I run gym. So I resort to wrapping another pair of set_info_plist_value steps around gym in my Fastfile like so:   # Set build version  (A)   build_number = number_of_commits   set_info_plist_value(path: 'MakeEatSeeApp/Info.plist'  key: 'CFBundleVersion'  value: build_number.to_s)    gym(     workspace: workspace      scheme: scheme      configuration: configuration      output_directory: '/tmp'      output_name: output_name   )    # Reset the build version  (B)   set_info_plist_value(path: 'MakeEatSeeApp/Info.plist'  key: 'CFBundleVersion'  value: "GIT_COMMIT_COUNT") When I run this  the value of CFBundleVersion sure enough gets updated as I desired: GIT_COMMIT_COUNT    # this value is checked into Git 12345                               # Xcode Build Phase replaces GIT_COMMIT_COUNT with `git rev-list --count HEAD` GIT_COMMIT_COUNT    # end of Xcode Build Phases  sets the value back 12345                               # Fastlane's set_info_plist_value doing its magic (A) above GIT_COMMIT_COUNT   ?# end of lane: set_info_plist_value sets it back again.  So all is well  except I get this undesired diff as a side-effect: -<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd"> +<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple Computer//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd"> What can I do here? :(

Issue 1424 : Fastlane action verify_build making invalid assertion ， Issue #1424 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Hey All  I've been playing with the new verify_build action (we were very excited to see it as we have our own custom scripts that do something similar). I don't believe the following exception is valid: raise "Inconsistent identifier found" unless plist['Entitlements']['application-identifier'] == "#{values['team_identifier']}.#{values['bundle_identifier']}"  Our app's bundle identifier is not prefixed by our team identifier but is prefixed with another value. This makes the entire action unusable since the exception is raised regardless of whether or not you passed in 'bundle_identifier' to be verified.

Issue 2670 : Update Product Bundle Identifier When Using update_info_plist ， Issue #2670 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description Updating the Bundle Identifier via the update_info_plist action will result in an error when uploading an app with a Distribution provisioning profile because the identifier will not match the Product Bundle Identifier value in Build Settings -> Packaging -> Product Bundle Identifier. The error will occur when uploading via Pilot or Deliver. From the Xcode 7.0 release notes: The new build setting Product Bundle Identifier (PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER) is the recommended place to set the Bundle Identifier for a target. The target¨s Info.plist should be configured to use this build setting by referencing it as $(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER) in the value for the CFBundleIdentifier key. Xcode offers to configure this for you when you accept the ＾Upgrade to recommended settings￣ project modernization in the issue navigator  unless your target preprocesses its Info.plist file. In that case you will need to configure this setting manually. This change is backwards-compatible to older versions of Xcode. This change is required to make certain features work  such as On Demand Resources  if your target preprocesses its Info.plist file. Issue 2746 : pass also regional settings at building ， Issue #2746 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Original issue by @MichaelRohs - Imported from fastlane/snapshot#4 Currently snapshot passes the language at building. This provides screenshots in different languages  which is one of the top benefits of snapshot. When the app displays fields like date  time and amount  it would be appropriate to set also the corresponding region. Otherwise you will receive screenshots with german texts and dates in US date format or vice versa  for example. Thanks.

Issue 3361 : Specified destination not in list of valid destinations ， Issue #3361 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Original issue by @nmccann - Imported from fastlane/scan#17 Hi  I recently attempted to migrate my Fastfile from using Xcodebuild to using Scan  but encountered the following error on our CI server: Unable to find a destination matching the provided destination specifier. Our server has a large number of devices  and I was able to find that the ID Scan was looking for belonged to a device with an older version of iOS - one that wasn't supported by my app. This appears to be caused by only filtering based on the device's name (as seen on this line)  rather than a combination of it's name and desired version. Ideally this the desired version could be determined automatically  perhaps based on the deployment target. As a simpler alternative it could be passed as a parameter. Thank you for your time and the excellent suite of tools! Noah

Issue 3644 : frameit: undefined method `find' for nil:NilClass ， Issue #3644 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub When trying to frame some single screenshots with frameit  each screenshot gives me the following error; undefined method `find' for nil:NilClass  This looks like something @philipengberg mentioned in #1739  though I'm unsure if he solved it. I keep coming getting these git-diff "thingys" all the time: -<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd"> +<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple Computer//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">  It looks like its stripping Computer out of the plist. - I'm not 100% sure this is the culprit but I am running that function (a lot) and I think besides xcode its the only thing touching the plist file. I'll try to look in more detail tomorrow.

Issue 3720 : New Action Template uses deprecated `is_string` param ， Issue #3720 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub When you create a new action using fastlane new_action  the action that is produced from the template uses the is_string parameter to FastLaneCore::ConfigItem. Issue 3797 : oclint action missing -p parameter and compile_commands.json fails on file relative paths  ， Issue #3797 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist [ X] Updated fastlane to the latest version [ X] I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description oclint action missing -p parameter It cause oclint fails when compile_commands.json is not in parent hierarchy of first input file. compile_commands.json fails on file relative paths "file" attribute  retrieved from compile_commands.json  may be not absolute. The full path need to be generated using also the "directory" attribute  in this case we need to concat the directory + file attribute i.e. xcpretty generates compile_commands.json with directory and file name to be concat. Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used this xcpretty compile_commands.json (doesn't work with current version) this xctool compile_commands.json (works with current version)

Issue 3906 : Fastlane gym should force signing with profile from sigh ， Issue #3906 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description This is a follow-up to #1393. For my use case  manually setting the provisioning profile in the code signing section to an env variable including the app_identifier won't work because I'm working on a white-label app where the app_identifier is selected at build time from hundreds of potential app_identifiers. I don't see any reason why fastlane couldn't update the pbxproj settings directly as update_app_identifier does. This is what fastlane's all about  using the suite of tools and having it "just work". So if sigh generates a provisioning profile  gym should automatically use it and currently that's not the case even though it finds lane_context[Actions::SharedValues::SIGH_PROFILE_PATH] it's not actually used if the corresponding UDIDs aren't updated in the xcodeproj's pbxproj. I'm currently using this custom action to definitively set the provisioning profile. def set_provisioning_profile(params)   info_plist_key = 'INFOPLIST_FILE'   identifier_key = 'PROVISIONING_PROFILE'    path = File.expand_path(File.join(ENV['PWD']  params[:xcodeproj]))   project = Xcodeproj::Project.open(path)    # Fetch the build configuration objects   configs = project.objects.select { |obj| obj.isa == 'XCBuildConfiguration' && !obj.build_settings[identifier_key].nil? }   raise "Info plist uses $(#{identifier_key})  but xcodeproj does not".red unless configs.count > 0    configs = configs.select { |obj| obj.build_settings[info_plist_key] == params[:plist_path] }   raise "Xcodeproj doesn't have configuration with info plist #{params[:plist_path]}.".red unless configs.count > 0    # For each of the build configurations  set app identifier   configs.each do |c|     puts c.build_settings[identifier_key].blue     c.build_settings[identifier_key] = params[:udid]   end    # Write changes to the file   project.save    UI.success("Updated #{params[:xcodeproj]} ?.") end @KrauseFx perhaps this could be added as another action or integrated more tightly into sigh / gym? Environment fastlane version (fastlane -v): 1.67.0 Do you use bundler  rbenv or rvm? bundler

Issue 3996 : team_id supplied to match does not trickle down to its cert and sigh calls if the project has another team_id set ， Issue #3996 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub It looks like the sigh and cert commands executed by match ignore the team identifier supplied to match and defaults to the default team identifier in the Appfile instead. The project is one where one whitelabel app has has a build target per label and each label has its own Apple Developer Team. So I use a fastlane match to make sure I have all the certificates necessary for all the labels. Appfile app_identifier "com.companyA.iphonedev" apple_id "devs@noodlewerk.com" team_id "AAAAAAAAAA"  Matchfile git_url "git@our.repository.com:certificates_A.git"  Fastfile lane :match do ... snipped other labels ...   match(type: "development"  app_identifier: "com.companyB.iphonedev"  team_id: "BBBBBBBBBB"  git_url: "git@our.repository.com:certificates_B.git") ... snipped other labels ... end  | false                                                | | shallow_clone         | false                                                | | force_for_new_devices | false Issue 4049 : spaceship on master: sigh doesn't work without iTunes Connect account ， Issue #4049 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Hi  Shortly: Sine sigh 1.6.x it is not possible to download provisioning profile using Apple ID which doesn't have access to iTines Connect. If the Apple ID has access to the iTunes Connect it is possible to download or create provisioning profile using sigh  this is normal behaviour. But in my case  I've special user (Apple ID) which has only access to Member Center / Developer Program which is used to download provisioning profiles and use them in the Jenkins node. Issue 4064 : [Fastlane] Cocoapods Repo Update ， Issue #4064 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description It looks like cocoapods has changed the default behavior of the install commands in the latest betas due to the Github Meta Issue. The repo-update parameter must now be included if you want to update the specs repo: From Cocoapods Changelog Running pod install doesn't imply an automatic spec repo update. The old behavior can be achieved by passing in the option --repo-update or running pod repo update. Marius Rackwitz #5004  Remove the configuration variable skip_repo_update as the default behavior varies now between pod install and pod (update|outdated). Marius Rackwitz #5017

Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used $ fastlane run verify_xcode [12:42:27]: -------------------------- [12:42:27]: --- Step: verify_xcode --- [12:42:27]: -------------------------- [12:42:27]: Verifying your Xcode installation at path '/Applications/Xcode-7.2.1.app'... Issue 4088 : update_app_identifier is saving the Project.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj in XML format ， Issue #4088 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description After upgrading to Xcode 7.3  when running fastlane and trying to get the new build number by executing increment_build_number action we started getting the error below. After some research we've found that after running update_app_identifier action the format of the project.pbxproj changed to XML while the one supported by agvtool it seems to be some sort for Json format now  so running increment_build_number or get_version_number won't no longer work as they are wrappers of agvtool. This issue has appeared after migrating to Xcode 7.3  it seems before that was not an issue for agvtool or something. So even if you try to run agvtool next-version -allor even agvtool what-version -terse manually  after a update_app_identifier action  they won't work as it's changing the format of the project.pbxproj file and avgtoolis not able to read it and returns 6. After further look at update_app_identifier.rb it seems that it's parsing the project.pbxproj as XML  therefore when it saves it back it's saving it as XML (not 100% sure here). Issue 4114 : Different position of padded frame due to title's character height ， Issue #4114 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Example Situation Having two titles for two screenshots (same device  same resolution). One title contains characters with descenders extending the baseline (g  p  j  q  y). The other title does not. Example titles to reproduce the issue: "Product" <- no descenders below baseline at all "Catalog" <- descender to the baseline due to "g" See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X-height for details about that part of typography. Used Font is: Open Sans Expected Use the padding as "offset" and always start at the same position to create a homogeneous layout ready for the Apple App Store ;) Actual The position is shifted. Seeing the screenshots in the store would be unbalanced  as they are presented in a scrollview side-by-side. framefile.json {     "default": {         "keyword": {             "font": "./fonts/Open_Sans/OpenSans-Bold.ttf"              "color": "#df0a25"         }          "title": {             "font": "./fonts/Open_Sans/OpenSans-Light.ttf"              "color": "#515151"         }          "background": "./background.jpg"          "padding": 70     }       "data": [] }  title.strings "Products" = "Product catalog"; "Selector" = "Product selector";   Environment frameit 2.5.1 Screenshots Source of the Problem In editor.rb line 246 ImageMagick's (better MiniMagick's) .gravity property is used to position the text. From: http://www.imagemagick.org/Usage/annotating/#gravity_text There is one very important difference between positioning images and text. If you draw a text string  without defining any form of "-gravity"  the string will be drawn relative to the 'baseline' of the font. In turn  using gravity will fight with the baseline as seen in the screenshots and leading to unbalanced text heights returned. The logic of trimming of the title in editor.rb line 251 is the source of the problem. Probably take the notes regarding .gravity from above into account. Looking forward to discuss this.

Issue 4134 : Typo in Provisioning Profile UUID keys (from sigh) ， Issue #4134 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description fastlane contains a typo for environment variables and references to provisioning profile UUIDs. Several places in the docs  this appears (for example  in the old codesigning guide): To fill the profile in using environment variables use PROVISIONING_PROFILE = "$(PROFILE_UUID)";  This allows the Xcode project to use Automatic provisioning profiles and enables fastlane to set a custom profile. In your Fastfile  add the following between your sigh and gym call: sigh  # use the UDID of the newly created provisioning profile ENV["PROFILE_UUID"] = lane_context[SharedValues::SIGH_UDID]  gym(scheme: "Release")  My fastfile  as seen below  instead references: ENV["PROFILE_UDID"] = lane_context[SharedValues::SIGH_UDID]  A quick search of the fastlane repo still turns up several instances of "UDID": fastlane/docs/Advanced.md 177:lane_context[SharedValues::SIGH_UDID]                 # The UDID of the generated provisioning profile  fastlane/docs/CodeSigning.md 43:ENV["PROFILE_UUID"] = lane_context[SharedValues::SIGH_UDID]  fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/sigh.rb 6:      SIGH_UDID = :SIGH_UDID 25:          Actions.lane_context[SharedValues::SIGH_UDID] = ENV["SIGH_UDID"] if ENV["SIGH_UDID"] # The UDID of the new profile 29:          return ENV["SIGH_UDID"] # return the UDID of the new profile  fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/update_project_code_signing.rb 43:                                       default_value: ENV["SIGH_UDID"])  fastlane/spec/actions_specs/sigh_spec.rb 12:        ENV["SIGH_UDID"] = "udid"  sigh/lib/sigh/local_manage.rb 18:      profile_filename = ENV["SIGH_UDID"] + ".mobileprovision"  sigh/lib/sigh/manager.rb 39:      ENV["SIGH_UDID"] = udid if udid  Should this be UUID? Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used N/A Configuration Files Please copy the complete content of your Fastfile and any other configuration files you use below: Fastfile: lane :build_app do |options|   # Fetch the latest ad-hoc profile:   # For more information: https://codesigning.guide   match(type: options.fetch(:match_profile_type  "adhoc"))   # use the UDID of the newly created provisioning profile   ENV["PROFILE_UDID"] = lane_context[SharedValues::SIGH_UDID]    # build the app.   gym(     use_legacy_build_api: true    ) end  Environment fastlane version (fastlane -v): fastlane 1.81.0 Do you use bundler  rbenv or rvm? Issue 4287 : [sigh] AppIdentifierPrefix entry not updated by resign command ， Issue #4287 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description While resigning .ipa file with resign command and underlying resign.sh bash script  the AppIdnetifierPrefix entry in the resigned app's Info.plist is not updated. As a result  after resigning Enterprise build for App Store distribution  the AppIdentifierPrefix is not updated and App Store build contains Enterprise app ID prefix. Reproduction Steps Use Enterprise distribution credentials to build .ipa file Enterprise app identifier prefix: 12345678 Enterprise team ID: 12345678 The Info.plist of built .ipa has ApplicationIdentifierPrefix entry set to 12345678 Resign enterprise .ipa using sigh for App Store distribution using new provisioning profile App Store app identifier prefix in new profile: ABCDEFGH App Store team ID in new profile: ABCDEFGH Check Info.plist of resigned .ipa Expected ApplicationIdentifierPrefix value: ABCDEFGH Actual ApplicationIdentifierPrefix value: 12345678 resign.sh did not update ApplicationIdentifierPrefix entry. The script reads new ApplicationIdentifierPrefix from provisioning profile on line 363  but never writes it back to the app Info.plist. Just like CFBundleIdentifier and other keys  the ApplicationIdentifierPrefix has to be updated to new value. Environment sigh version: 1.6.1 Do you use bundler to execute sigh: yes Do you use a Ruby environment manager: rvm

Issue 4336 : Integer ConfigItems always default to zero ， Issue #4336 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines ? Issue Description ConfigItem incorrectly causes all instances with data_type Integer to default to 0. The issue is the auto_convert_value method on ConfigItem. If the data_type is Integer  that method unconditionally casts value to Integer. Casting nil to Integer results in 0  not nil. That means that by the time that control reaches here  value is not nil  so the default value is not properly substituted. A specific example of the bug is in pilot's wait_processing_interval parameter. It should default to 30  but instead it is read as 0 here  in the BuildManager. As a result  the sleep has no effect  and instead just loops as fast as possible  constrained only by the response time of iTunes Connect  which is about a second in my tests. You can see the evidence of this issue in my log output  below: [12:05:25]: Waiting for iTunes Connect to process the new build [12:05:27]: Waiting for iTunes Connect to process the new build [12:05:28]: Waiting for iTunes Connect to process the new build [12:05:29]: Waiting for iTunes Connect to process the new build [12:05:30]: Waiting for iTunes Connect to process the new build  showing that we're hitting iTunes Connect about once per second  instead of the intended default once per thirty seconds. The fix should be pretty straightforward  and I may even take a swing at it after #3888. We'll want to check all ConfigItems that use the type Integer  though  to make sure we're not introducing any regressions. Issue 4397 : [sigh] Resigning without explicit entitlements looses keychain access group information ， Issue #4397 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated sigh to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description Scenario 1: Resigning Expired Enterprise IPA Input: Expired IPA built for Enterprise distribution (provisioning profile has expired) IPA was codesigned with entitlements that included keychain-access-group value like this: New provisioning profile New provisioning profile has keychain-access-group value as follows: This is standard for provisioning profiles to look like this No original entitlements file Why this is the case is another question  let's assume this is the situation we have to deal with. When resigning with sigh resign  the resign.sh script doesn't find entitlements and extracts them from provided provisioning profile. The resigned IPA then contains keychain access group value different from the original IPA. As a result  new IPA will not be able to access shared keychain values created by previous IPA. This is serious issue and will show up while testing upgrade scenario. Detailed picture: Scenario 2: Resigning Enterprise IPA for App Store distribution This scenario is similar to Scenario 1. The only difference is that IPA is now resigned for App Store distribution  changing bundle identifier  app prefix  team ID and other values in the process. Here again  the new IPA will have keychain access group like APPSTORETEAMID.* and will be incompatible with previous App Store version  which was resigned by another script  not sigh. Proposed Fix The proposed fix is to extract entitlements both from new provisioning profile and from current app. Extracting entitlements form the app is possible with command like this: /usr/bin/codesign -d --entitlements entitlements.plist Payload/MyApp.app. The provisioning profile entitlements keychain-access-group entry should then be replaced with the value from the app's entitlements. Next  the app identifier prefix in keychain access group needs to be replaced with value from provisioning profile's entitlements. This is important when resigning from Enterprise to App Store. Overview: Environment sigh version: 1.6.1 Do you use bundler to execute sigh: yes Do you use a Ruby environment manager: rvm

Issue 4427 : [Pilot] Multiple Platform Build Support/tvOS Universal Apps ， Issue #4427 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description When uploading builds to a universal tvOS app  I constantly run into the issue: pilot/lib/pilot/build_manager.rb:91:in `wait_for_processing_build': [!] undefined method `train_version' for nil:NilClass (NoMethodError) When traced down I believe a contributing factor is I can submit two ipas  with the same build number  version and app id in order for it to be a universal app on the App Store. Currently Pilot only filters for processing builds with the App Version  Build Number and App Id  but it should also be filtering builds by platform  which is available in each respective build data. Another contributing issue to this could be that when I run: bundle exec pilot builds Not all of my builds show. For example here is the iTunes Connect Data and the respective pilot output: It looks as though the pilot list command is only showing one of the build trains which in this case is the tvOS one. When I currently encounter the above issue it is when I try to upload the iOS version so I am wondering if it is because pilot is only recognizing the tvOS build train.

Issue 4482 : frameit picks up mock frames if fastlane cloned on the same level with ios project ， Issue #4482 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description If fastlane is cloned at the same level with iOS project  i.e.: /Users/me/projects/fastlane /Users/me/projects/my_ios_project then frameit will pick mock frames from fastlane/frameit/spec/fixtures/mock_frames instead of ~/.frameit/devices_frames https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/frameit/lib/frameit/template_finder.rb#L62 As far as I understand  this code requests frameit to search for templates on one level above the project folder. fastlane 1.83.0 frameit 2.6.0

Issue 4524 : fastlane 1.85.0 crashing on Travis due to Ruby update ， Issue #4524 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description Yesterday morning  fastlane worked fine on Travis. Today  it's segfaulting  without any changes to fastlane config or .travis.yml. It's because Travis updated their xcode7.3 image to use ruby-2.0.0-p648 by default. I haven't tested this locally  but switching Travis back to use 2.0.0-p643 (the build it was using yesterday) fixed the problem. Unfortunately  I don't have more time to dig into this right but I do have a workaround: add this to .travis.yml: rvm:   - 2.0.0-p643 Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace Issue 4642 : Specific order of profiles required in some cases when resigning binary with extension ， Issue #4642 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub This issue resides within resign.sh. Let's say I have a binary Experiments.ipa with the bundle identifier com.company.experiments. Within this app I have an extension called AudioPlugin  which has the bundle identifier com.company.experiments.AudioPlugin. I also have a profile Experiments.mobileprovision that has a wildcard bundle identifier  and a profile for the extension called AudioPlugin.mobileprovision with a bundle identifier that is the same as the extension. In order to resign Experiments.ipa  I run the following: sigh resign --signing_identity "iPhone Distribution: Company Pty Ltd" --provisioning_profile Experiments.mobileprovision --provisioning_profile com.company.experiments.AudioPlugin=AudioPlugin.mobileprovision  This doesn't work: the extension is signed with Experiments.mobileprovision because somewhere within resign.sh the wildcard identifier is matched to the extension. However  changing the order of the two --provisioning_profile flags values works as expected. I feel that this should either be fixed so that a profile that exactly matched a bundle identifier will be used even if there is a wildcard profile available. Or  this issue should be clearly documented so other developers are aware that the profile order determines precedence

Issue 4673 : frameit requires a PSD to be in the devices folder to run ， Issue #4673 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version (1.89.0) I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description Frameit will not run unless there¨s a PSD file in the devices folder. This is a pain when you already have converted the PSD files and don¨t want to keep them around (to save space + to keep the directory neater). Enhancement request Check for existence of one or more PNGs instead and continue with framing if they¨re found. Workaround In the meanwhile  here¨s a one-pixel PSD and the corresponding PNG that will skip the PSD check without your having to have all the Apple PSDs in the directory: skip-device-installation.zip

Issue 4674 : Deliver has issues handling filenames with multiple seperators. ， Issue #4674 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description Deliver has issues parsing certain filenames with multiple file separators. One example of a file name it can't understand is this: 1_watch_1.Slack for iOS Upload-1.png.jpeg It instead interprets this as: 1_watch_1.Slack This means it can't find the file and throws an error due to not being able to figure out the MIME type. Usually your screenshots would be named better than this however when deliver was set up it downloaded the existing iTunes screenshots with their original filenames which caused more issues. As a workaround I simply removed the original filename from the file name however Fastlane didn't understand the "jpeg" file extension  upon renaming it to "jpg" it worked. So to recap: Deliver should be able to handle complex file names like "1_watch_1.Slack for iOS Upload-1.png.jpeg" Deliver should be able to understand the "jpeg" file extension. Perhaps another issue could be opened to make deliver download existing screenshots with sensible names "1_watch_1.jpeg" rather than "1_watch_1.Slack for iOS Upload-1.png.jpeg" Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used Unknown content-type for file ./fastlane/screenshots/en-au/1_watch_1.slack for ios upload-1.png.jpeg  Configuration Files Isn't a issue with the Fastfile Environment fastlane version (run fastlane -v): 1..87.0 Do you use bundler to execute fastlane (i.e. bundle exec fastlane)? no Do you use a Ruby environment manager (e.g. chruby  rbenv  rvm)? RVM

Issue 4700 : Gradle Action - Properties with special characters not supported ， Issue #4700 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Issue Description When using the properties attributes in the gradle actions  we can not have properties that contains special characters like spaces or quotes. My use case is a property that is filled with a user-specified text : the release notes of the build. The user can enter any character including spaces  \n and quotes. Those should all be accepted. Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used Fastlane line : fastlane beta release_note:'Release note test' Last command executed : gradlew app:crashlyticsUploadDistributionRelease -p . -PRELEASE_NOTE=Release note test Output : FAILURE: Build failed with an exception. What went wrong: Task 'note' not found in root project ''. Configuration Files desc "Submit a new Beta Build to Crashlytics Beta"   lane :beta do |options|     gradle(         task: 'clean'       )       gradle(         task: 'assemble'          build_type: 'Release'       )       gradle(         task: 'app:crashlyticsUploadDistribution'          build_type: 'Release'          properties: {           'RELEASE_NOTE' => options[:release_note]         }        )   end  Environment fastlane version (run fastlane -v): fastlane 1.89.0 Do you use bundler to execute fastlane (i.e. bundle exec fastlane)? No Do you use a Ruby environment manager (e.g. chruby  rbenv  rvm)? No Proposed Fix Usually  when using Gradle directly with properties  they are surrounded with double quotes to prevent those kind of errors. Example : gradlew "-PRELEASE_NOTE=Release note test" clean app:assembleRelease app:crashlyticsUploadDistributionRelease Quick fix : Line 38 of https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/gradle.rb flags << params[:properties].map { |k  v| "-P#{k}=#{v}" }.join(' ') unless params[:properties].nil? should become flags << params[:properties].map { |k  v| "'-P#{k}=#{v}'" }.join(' ') unless params[:properties].nil? Ideally  we should also unescape single quotes in k and v to prevent any errors.

Issue 4823 : Exporting iOS app archive replaces embedded provisioning profile with older version ， Issue #4823 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description I¨m using match to manage provisioning profiles and have set up the Xcode project to use the sigh environment variables to select the correct profile. Building the app works fine and looking at the embedded.mobileprovision file inside the app in the Xcode archive generated by running match + gym  I?can see that the correct (latest) profile was used. However  when the IPA is exported by gym using xcodebuild -exportArchive  the embedded.mobileprovision inside the IPA is replaced with another older version of the profile with the same name ("match AdHoc appid") that is installed on the system. I can reproduce this by manually running the archive step on the same xcarchive like this: /usr/bin/xcrun /Library/Ruby/Gems/2.0.0/gems/gym-1.6.3/lib/assets/wrap_xcodebuild/xcbuild-safe.sh -exportArchive -exportOptionsPlist 'path/to/gym_config.plist' -archivePath 'path/to/My App.xcarchive' -exportPath 'path/to/gym_output'  I read that with Xcode 7 exportArchive should be using the profile from the archive  but that does not seem to be the case here. Since the provisioning_profile_path is no longer supported  I don¨t see another option to tell exportArchive which profile to use. Deleting the older profile from my system resolves the issue. This seems to be more of an Xcode issue  but I was hoping for possible pointers on how to best resolve this short of manually deleting the match provisioning profiles from the system before running fastlane. Thanks! Environment Xcode version: 7.3.1 fastlane version (run fastlane -v): 1.90.0 Do you use bundler to execute fastlane (i.e. bundle exec fastlane)? No. Do you use a Ruby environment manager (e.g. chruby  rbenv  rvm)? No.

Issue 4866 : Match fails to import certificates when using a fully-qualified path to the keychain ， Issue #4866 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Issue Description In match/lib/match/utils.rb there's a hard-coded path to ~/Library/Keychains prepended to the keychain "name". fastlane/match/lib/match/utils.rb Line 4 in 5dff30d command = "security import #{item_path.shellescape} -k ~/Library/Keychains/#{keychain.shellescape}" When using a fully-specified path to the keychain  for example using Jenkins' "Keychains and Provisioning Profiles" plugin  the path ends up getting augmented incorrectly. A sanitized example from my project: security import /var/folders/t4/99vplf817qs40m8tz1tkkj500000gn/T/d20160526-57929-19soscm/certs/distribution/xxxx.cer -k ~/Library/Keychains//Users/user/.jenkins-slave/workspace/iOS\ Parameterized\ Build/jenkins_match.keychain -T /usr/bin/codesign -T /usr/bin/security&> /dev/null  FastlaneCore::CertChecker can handle this situation correctly  so perhaps some similar techniques can be applied to the match implementation to fix this. It would also be nice to avoid sending output from the import process to /dev/null  at least when running in verbose mode. That would make the failure easier to see. Possibly related to #4826

Issue 5109 : update_project_team fails unless team has been set first ， Issue #5109 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub This line (gsub(/DevelopmentTeam...) assumes a DevelopmentTeam exists fastlane/fastlane/lib/fastlane/actions/update_project_team.rb Line 15 in 9c0494e File.write(path  p.gsub(/DevelopmentTeam = .*;/  "DevelopmentTeam = #{params[:teamid]};")) But new projects with Team is set to 'None' don't have that key  e.g.:                 TargetAttributes = {                     0A1CA8F01D0B76B8005D5B89 = {                         CreatedOnToolsVersion = 7.3.1;                     };                 };  Projects created with an older version of Xcode  e.g. a freshly initialized React Native project which uses a stale project  the app target is not present. In that case the main app target needs to be looked up  something like this (I'm not a Ruby programmer...) main_target = xcproj.targets.find { |t| t.name == project_name } main_target_uuid = main_target && main_target.uuid if main_target_uuid   # add to TargetAttributes with the uuid as the key and DevelopmentTeam inside end I realize that this is due to limitations in the xcodeproj gem  and I've submitted a sister issue there  but they have over 30 open issues so it's not likely that there will be a quick solution on their side. For now  I'll do my own gsub on the project file and avoid update_project_team... thanks!

Issue 5389 : Unable to patch `PackageApplication` script bundled in Xcode 8 beta. ， Issue #5389 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description When gym has use_legacy_build_api set to true  Xcode's PackageApplication perl script is patched to be able to create the IPA from the archive. Issue 5669 : [sigh] Embedded mobileprovision in framework bundles is not updated while resigning ， Issue #5669 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description When using PROVISIONING_PROFILE option for xcodebuild command  an embedded.mobileprovision is added to all dynamic frameworks. In my case I'm using CocoaPods with use_frameworks! configuration option. With PROVISIONING_PROFILE xcodebuild -workspace MyProject.xcworkspace -scheme MyScheme -configuration Release PROVISIONING_PROFILE="my-profile-UUID"  So when "Embed Pods Frameworks" build phase is running  I can see embedded.mobileprovision present in all frameworks  e.g. building file list ... done SVProgressHUD.framework/ SVProgressHUD.framework/Info.plist SVProgressHUD.framework/embedded.mobileprovision SVProgressHUD.framework/SVProgressHUD ... SVProgressHUD.framework/_CodeSignature/ SVProgressHUD.framework/_CodeSignature/CodeResources I believe this is how xcodebuild works when PROVISIONING_PROFILE option is specified - it just embeds it into anything that has bundle ID  including frameworks. This is how it looks in the IPA: Without PROVISIONING_PROFILE xcodebuild -workspace MyProject.xcworkspace -scheme MyScheme -configuration Release  This time there is no provisioning profile embedded into framework. I think that's because automatic lookup finds no profile matching framework's bundle ID. How Does It Relate to Sigh? Basically  when resigning an app using sigh resign action  the embedded.mobileprovision inside .framework bundles is neither updated nor removed. So when uploading such resigned app to iTC it comes back with errors like this: ERROR ITMS-90179: "Invalid Code Signing. The executable 'Payload/MyApp.app/Frameworks/AFNetworking.framework/AFNetworking' must be signed with the certificate that is contained in the provisioning profile." After resigning  signing identity  team ID and profile UUID have changed  except for those "extra" embedded.mobileprovision inside frameworks. Suggested Fix? It does feel like Xcode is doing us a bad service by sticking that profile everywhere  on the other hand it kind of makes sense since we explicitly used PROVISIONING_PROFILE option. For the app I'm currently working on  the CI setup is a bit of legacy and I can't just rewrite scripts and get rid of that option. So I guess sigh resign could take care of this problem  i.e. remove all embedded mobile provisioning profiles from all .framework bundles before resigning them. After all  those profiles inside frameworks make no sense at all. ... waiting when we can move to Xcode 8 with signing not required any more for frameworks :) Environment cocoapods: 1.0.0 fastlane: 1.99.0 sigh: 1.6.0 bundle exec: yes rvm: yes

Issue 5696 : Deliver creates default metadata/screenshot folder to ./fastlane not to ./.fastlane ， Issue #5696 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description Conditions: I use fastlane from the hidden ".fastlane" folder. I use deliver from fastlane using skip_screenshots: true. I don't specify a custom path for screenshots. If I run it  deliver creates the empty screenshots folder to ./fastlane/screenshots and not to ./.fastlane/screenshots. So I will have 2 fastlane folders: ./.fastlane: with all the necessary files ./fastlane: with only the empty screenshots folder On the next run I get the following message: Could not find fastlane in current directory. Would you like to set it up? (y/n) Because fastlane thinks that it should use the - actually empty - ./fastlane folder. The error might be around here: https://github.com/fastlane/fastlane/blob/master/deliver/lib/deliver/detect_values.rb#L35 We might also consider not to create the screenshots folder if skip_screenshots: true. Thanks!

Issue 5700 : SimulatorZoomFix: Replace more than just whitespace characters (due to iPad Pro names) ， Issue #5700 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Issue Description An iphonesimulator device with name "iPad Pro (9.7 inch)" will (after launch) add a key SimulatorWindowLastScale-com.apple.CoreSimulator.SimDeviceType.iPad-Pro--9-7-inch-. The character replacement last modified in fastlane-old/snapshot@9f0822f only replaces whitespace. Presumptively  I was going to make a PR for・ simulator_name = simulator.name.tr(   '^' + # replace all characters except ones included below   ('a'.upto('z').to_a + 'A'.upto('Z').to_a + '0'.upto('9').to_a).join('')     "-" ) ・but  then I launched an "iPad Pro (12.9 inch)" simulator device (with Xcode 8S193k) and a key for SimulatorWindowLastScale-com.apple.CoreSimulator.SimDeviceType.iPad-Pro appeared at the bottom of the dict  so that's probably too na?ve. Todo Test older Xcode versions to see if the key for the original 12.9 inch iPad Pro has always been SimulatorWindowLastScale-com.apple.CoreSimulator.SimDeviceType.iPad-Pro. Then  I｀ll write a switch statement  based on findings. Worry about future device names・ ? See also: #5673 (comment)

Issue 5909 : gym: When output_name contains "/" (directory character)  export fails ， Issue #5909 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description When the value of output_name contains a slash(/)  xcodebuild will create directories underneath the archive path. Then when gym attempts to export the archive and dSYM  it will potentially fail if any of the directories do not exist under the export path. Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used +----------------------+------------------------------+ |                Summary for gym 1.7.0                | +----------------------+------------------------------+ | output_name          | feature/some_feature         | | scheme               | feature-dev                  | | export_method        | enterprise                   | | include_bitcode      | false                        | | output_directory     | '/Users/user/export'         | | project              | ./feature.xcodeproj          | | destination          | generic/platform=iOS         | | clean                | false                        | | silent               | false                        | | use_legacy_build_api | false                        | +----------------------+------------------------------+  set -o pipefail && xcodebuild -scheme feature-dev \ -project ./feature.xcodeproj \ -destination 'generic/platform=iOS' \ -archivePath \ '/Users/user/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives/2016-08-26/feature/some_feature 2016-08-26 11.20.45.xcarchive' ... [11:22:38]: $ cd '/Users/user/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives/2016-08-26/feature/some_feature 2016-08-26 11.20.45.xcarchive/dSYMs' && zip -r '/Users/user/export/feature/some_feature.app.dSYM.zip' *.dSYM [11:22:38]: ? zip I/O error: No such file or directory [11:22:38]: ? zip error: Could not create output file (/Users/user/export/feature/some_feature.app.dSYM.zip)  The work around is to ensure the output_name does not contain any slash characters. However  should gym either: Convert any slashes(/) to dash(-) or underscore(_) in output_name  before passing archive path to xcodebuild. Attempt to create any directories under export_path  if any directories were created under archive_path. Environment fastlane version (run fastlane -v): fastlane 1.101.0 Do you use bundler to execute fastlane (i.e. bundle exec fastlane)? No Do you use a Ruby environment manager (e.g. chruby  rbenv  rvm)? No

Issue 5910 : Expose the provisioning profile name out of sigh/match to use it for Xcode 8 codesigning ， Issue #5910 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description With Xcode 8 the way to set the provisioning profile has changed. Instead of using the UUID of the profile  it uses the team_id/profile_name. As we have different environments we need to set the name dynamically. Unfortunately sigh/match only expose the UUID as evironment variable. Fix Additionally to the UUID also expose the profile_name as environment variable

Issue 6058 : Default ios_version for snapshot not sensitive to device limitations ， Issue #6058 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Issue Description iPhone 4s only supports up to iOS 9.x  while all the other device types needed for a full iTunesConnect screen size representation will work on iOS 10. For apps that support both iOS 9 and iOS 10  snapshot on the latest Xcode 8 setup doesn't succeed out of the box in a single run without creating custom simulators first. Calling snapshot reset_simulators clears everything out and reinstalls iOS 10-based simulators for most devices. This results in a case where setting ios_version '10.0' will fail on iPhone 4s  and setting ios_version '9.3' will fail on all other devices. Workaround In Xcode 8  manually create simulators for all devices for iOS 9.3  then run snapshot with the override ios_version '9.3' Configuration Files snapfile: devices([   "iPad Air"    "iPhone 4s"    "iPad Pro (12.9-inch)"    "iPhone 5"    "iPhone 6"    "iPhone 6 Plus" ])  languages([ "da"  "de-DE"  "el"  "en-AU"  "en-CA"  "en-GB"  "en-US"  "es-ES"  "fr-FR"  "it"  "ja"  "ko"  "nl"  "no"  "pt-BR"  "ru"  "sv"  "tr"  "zh-Hans"  "zh-Hant"])  scheme "Lightbow" stop_after_first_error true  output_directory "./Store/screenshots" clear_previous_screenshots true  ios_version '9.3' Environment snapshot 1.14.0  executed via just "snapshot" on the command line on macOS 10.11.6

Issue 6097 : [snapshot] Simulator not reset or app not reinstalled if `ios_version` is missing ， Issue #6097 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Issue Description Without specifying ios_version in Snapfile the simulator's device_udid will not be known to erase_simulator and reinstall_app. This results in e.g. following call being made which misses the device_udid [17:19:04]: $ xcrun simctl uninstall  com.pocketlifestyle.fretello.lead.dev &> /dev/null  No error is reported and the snapshotting continues as normally. In our case the UI test however requires the app to be reinstalled and will fail at a later stage. I've already did some digging in the code and the issue seems to be with the device_udid function of the TestCommandGenerator which does not check if a ios_version is available in the config. PR with a fix will follow shortly. Issue 6099 : Gym always cleans project  no way to set timeout to not be 10s ， Issue #6099 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description When running gym with the "--clean false" arguments  it still cleans project. If it takes longer than 10s (on very slow hard drive or while you are unzipping large files  etc.) it will never complete. Unfortunately there doesn't seem to be a way to set that 10s timeout  FASTLANE_XCODE_LIST_TIMEOUT environment variable doesn't do it. Issue 6138 : spaceship incorrectly reports "Successfully logged in to iTunes Connect" for a user who is not in iTunes Connect. ， Issue #6138 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description spaceship -u [my email] incorrectly reports "Successfully logged in to iTunes Connect" for a user who is not in iTunes Connect. When initializing a new project using fastlane init --verbose I received an "Unauthorized Access" error. During the debug process  I ran spaceship -u [my email]. This reported that it successfully logged in to iTunes Connect. See issue #6084 for more background. Within spaceship if I execute Spaceship::Tunes::Application.all I see an Unauthorized Access error  as I would expect. After some investigation  I determined that I had not been added to my company's iTunes Connect portal. After being added to iTunes Connect  Spaceship::Tunes::Application.all correctly returns the list of our applications. I have verified I am using the latest versions of fastlane and all dependencies  as well as the Xcode command-line tools. fastlane does not crash and I am able to continue with the manual steps once access fails. Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used Output when a user is not in iTunes Connect: $ spaceship -u xxx@xxx.com  Logging into to iTunes Connect (xxx@xxx.com)... Successfully logged in to iTunes Connect  Logging into the Developer Portal (xxx@xxx.com)... Successfully logged in to the Developer Portal  --------------------------------------- | Welcome to the spaceship playground | ---------------------------------------  Enter docs to open up the documentation Enter exit to exit the spaceship playground Enter _ to access the return value of the last executed command  Just enter the commands and confirm with Enter [1] pry(main)>   With no valid user  if I execute Spaceship::Tunes::Application.all I see an Unauthorized Access error  as I would expect. Issue 6207 : latest_testflight_build_number doesn't consider Invalid Binaries ， Issue #6207 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub OS X 10.11.6 fastlane 1.103.0 ruby 2.0.0p648 (2015-12-16 revision 53162) [universal.x86_64-darwin15] This is not a crash and there is nothing of real value in the Fastfile  or the scripts output. This is easiest to explain as follows: The Fastfile gets the latest build number from testflight using latest_testflight_build_number. This value is 14. The value is incremented and a build is made and uploaded to testflight and we wait for apple's response. (skip_waiting_for_build_processing is not set) The whole process succeeds and a build is available for download to testers. A second build is made using the same script. The build number is now 15  but because of an Invalid Binary error during upload (Entitlements in this case)  the binary is rejected. When any subsequent builds are made  they will fail. This is because the build number will again be set to 15. The problem is that latest_testflight_build_number only considers valid binaries (or Apple only considers valid binaries when returning the build number)  and thus the script will keep trying to upload the same build number. (15 in this case)

Issue 6219 : "Check Dependencies" error when building with Gym : Gym bug? Xcode 8? Travis? Human error?  ， Issue #6219 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description When building on Travis CI  I continue to get "check dependencies" errors when doing builds for Fabric Beta distribution (Enterprise builds)  with 2 of the 8 dependencies reporting a problem. The problem appears to be that manual code signing choices  for example a scheme which uses "iOS Distribution" identity with "Release" configuration"  is not being respected by some subprojects (which try to sign against "iOS Development" identity  despite explicitly setting to "iOS Distribution" in the main project) Using @tmm1 's advice  I spit out the gym log and finally see something that explains the situation (see "output" below). Basically I get two errors  depending on if I explicitly set codesigning_identity in Gym. If I do not set it  gym's log says it can't find a certificate for iOS Developer on this scheme  which is true. It doesn't exist and it never existed. If I do set it  I'm told (for example) AdjustSdk has conflicting provisioning settings. AdjustSdk is automatically signed  but code signing identity <<REDACTED>> has been manually specified. Running locally (running the same Fastlane lane "do_the_beta") I do not have this mysterious certificate in my local keychain  but fastlane builds for Fabric Beta without incident locally. I don't think that certificate has ever existed before for us. The BETA scheme with RELEASE configuration is set to  and should be using  "iOS Distribution " not "iOS Development" when doing our enterprise builds for Fabric Beta. Our project contains two submodules  but most dependencies are brought into the project via git subtree. It is my understanding that these subprojects can be left as-is with "automatic codesigning" and should inherit from the parent project. So  Adjust and iOS Reachability are trying to sign with "iOS Development" (which is the default build setting for these  and really all  of the subprojects imported)  but none of the other projects in the subtree express this problem: GRMustache SocketRocket Some private SDKs MBProgressHUD I'm having a really difficult time understanding how fastlane + gym + Xcode 8 + subproject dependencies + manual code sign works together  and what needs to be set in what way. Every documentation I read seems to assume a very simple  "set the main project targets to manual code signing". I assume this means I should be able to forget about subprojects and let the build system handle those  and yet here we are. I've looked at the Build Settings for all of the subprojects. They are  indeed  set to iOS Developer in the Code Signing Identify  but this is just the default for all of them and was not altered by our team. This just "how things have always been". If the main project is set to manual code signing  and these subprojects are set to "Automatic"  should that not override any other legacy settings? Or  and this would really suck  do we have to manually manage code signing for all subprojects from now on? That wouldn't make much sense to me  because code signing identities are relative to our schemes  and our schemes are unique to our project. Subprojects would have no knowledge of that. Add certificates to keychain         import_certificate(keychain_name: BUILD_KEYCHAIN  certificate_path: "#{CERTS_DIR_PATH}/apple.cer")         import_certificate(keychain_name: BUILD_KEYCHAIN  certificate_path: "#{CERTS_DIR_PATH}/dist.cer")         import_certificate(keychain_name: BUILD_KEYCHAIN  certificate_path: "#{CERTS_DIR_PATH}/dist.p12"  certificate_password: ENV['BETA_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD'])         import_certificate(keychain_name: BUILD_KEYCHAIN  certificate_path: "#{CERTS_DIR_PATH}/App_Store_Certificate.p12"  certificate_password: ENV['APPSTORE_CERTIFICATE_PASSWORD'])          # Copy all provisioning profiles to Xcode default directory (could be replaced with "sigh" command  maybe?)         sh("mkdir -p #{PROFILE_PATH}")         sh("cp #{PROFILE_DIR_PATH}/* #{PROFILE_PATH}")         sh("ls -l #{PROFILE_PATH}")     end      lane :run_test do         scan(scheme: SCHEME_BETA              configuration: 'Debug'              sdk: 'iphonesimulator10.0'              device: 'iPhone 6'         )     end      desc "Build and upload to Crashlytics Beta"      lane :do_the_beta do |options|          # set project team to enterprise account         update_project_team(path: PROJECT_FILE_PATH  teamid: TEAM_ID_ENTERPRISE)         set_info_plist_value(path: INFO_PLIST_PATH  key: 'SNBuildCommitIdentifier'  value: CURRENT_COMMIT)          # set default release notes and revision string         release_notes = Actions.sh('git log -1').chomp         revision = options[:build_number]         distribution_group = FABRIC_BASIC_DISTRIBUTION_GROUP          # set special release notes and revision for prototype and release branches         if CURRENT_BRANCH != nil && !CURRENT_BRANCH.empty?             if CURRENT_BRANCH.start_with?('prototype/')                      release_notes = "**PROTOTYPE** for #{CURRENT_BRANCH}\n#{release_notes}"                 revision = "PROTO-#{CURRENT_COMMIT}"                 distribution_group = FABRIC_PROTOTYPE_DISTRIBUTION_GROUP             elsif CURRENT_BRANCH.start_with?('release/')                 release_notes = "**RELEASE** for #{CURRENT_BRANCH}\n#{release_notes}"                 revision = "RELEASE-#{CURRENT_COMMIT}"             end         end          puts release_notes          #set build version for beta distribution ease-of-installation         set_info_plist_value(path: INFO_PLIST_PATH  key: 'CFBundleVersion'  value: revision)              #build the archive and ipa         gym(scheme: SCHEME_BETA              configuration: 'Release'              sdk: 'iphoneos'              use_legacy_build_api: true         )          #automatically uses the ipa from gym and env vars to fill in upload credentials         #distribute via crashlytics if it isn't a pull request         if !pull_request?             crashlytics(notes: release_notes  groups: [distribution_group])         end     end      def pull_request?         pr_number = ENV['TRAVIS_PULL_REQUEST']         pr_number != nil && !pr_number.empty? && pr_number != 'false'     end end Environment Travis CI  running latest Xcode 8 GM fastlane 1.103.0 fastlane core 0.52.0 Scan 0.13.0 Gym 1.9.0 Do you use bundler to execute fastlane (i.e. bundle exec fastlane)? Issue 6264 : runner.rb seems to be chdir'ing once extra in a rescue clause  causing a less meaningful exception ， Issue #6264 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub runner.rb recovers from an error in a clause which does a chdir into the fastlane folder by chdir'ing into the fastlane folder yet again. This is causing a backtrace that says "No such file or directory - {fastlane folder}" when that's not actually true  and thus masking the real issue. I suggest removing the Dir.chdir(path_to_use) wrapper block from the rescue clause starting on runner.rb:59. Issue 6278 : update_app_identifier and update_project_provisioning both change current directory  but do not change back when done ， Issue #6278 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description If you run the update_app_identifier or the update_project_provisioning action  they change directories from ${SRCROOT}/fastlane to ${SRCROOT}  but they never change back when they are done. This causes other code that looks for files in a specific path to always fail to find the file  and fastlane fails at that point. We run fastlane on multiple apps at once in a loop  so we're running these actions multiple times per lane execution. This only started happening recently  somewhere between fastlane 1.101 and 1.104. Complete output when running fastlane  including the stack trace and command used Prefer not to include  as it's sensitive. See example lane instead that reproduces issue  Configuration Files Please copy the complete content of your Fastfile and any other configuration files you use below: Fastfile:   # lane that reproduces issue:   lane :bug do       puts File.absolute_path(".")       # first time it's ${SRCROOT}/fastlane  second time it's ${SRCROOT}.       # It should always be one or the other (preferrably the first as that's how it worked before).        # replace with your own project info       proj = 'WayfairApp.xcodeproj'       plist = 'WayfairApp/Info.plist'       identifier = 'com.wayfair.WayfairApp'       target_pattern = '^WayfairApp$'        # problem action 1       update_app_identifier(xcodeproj: proj                              plist_path: plist                              app_identifier: identifier)       # problem action 2       cert       sigh(app_identifier: identifier)       update_project_provisioning(xcodeproj: proj                                    target_filter: target_pattern)        puts File.absolute_path(".")   end Environment fastlane version (run fastlane -v): fastlane 1.104.0 Do you use bundler to execute fastlane (i.e. bundle exec fastlane)? no Do you use a Ruby environment manager (e.g. chruby  rbenv  rvm)? rbenv  but happens on machines without it

Issue 6478 : Inconsistent ENV Variables used ， Issue #6478 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description Inconsistent environment variables are used throughout fastlane leading to duplicate entries for tools. action latest_testflight_build_number expects ITUNESCONNECT_USER Sigh expects SIGH_USERNAME Deliver expects DELIVER_USERNAME action set_changelog expect FASTLANE_USERNAME Credentials Manager expects FASTLANE_USER Produce expects DELIVER_USER or PRODUCE_USERNAME watchbuild expects FASTLANE_USER etc... Suggestion 1 Enforce standard naming of environment variables for per-tool settings {tool_name}_USERNAME {tool_name}_PASSWORD  which override any global settings  for example ITUNESCONNECT_USERNAME ITUNESCONNECT_PASSWORD (or use credential manager) MEMBERCENTER_USERNAME MEMBERCENTER_PASSWORD (or use credential manager)  or for using the same credentials for all Apple/iTunes related work FASTLANE_USERNAME FASTLANE_PASSWORD (or use credential manager)  Suggestion 2 Create documentation listing all global and tool-specific environment variables. I welcome some feedback and discussion on this.

Issue 6481 : S3 upload action builds invalid URL when region is us-east-1 ， Issue #6481 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Issue Description The s3 action has a hard-coded mechanism for determining the domain for the URL it generates for the installation plist file. It assumes that if you have a region configured  it should append that region name to the subdomain  e.g. s3-us-east-1.amazonaws.com for a region of us-east-1. This is a problem because the domain above is not valid  and the correct value is s3.amazonaws.com. The issue can be resolved by using the AWS SDK's internal ability to generate a valid hostname  as this pull request implements: #6344 Creating this issue post-hoc to ensure that it gets noticed :)

Issue 6626 : Failures due to presence of FASTLANE_PASSWORD ， Issue #6626 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description When FASTLANE_PASSWORD is present as an env var (configured on .zshrc or .bashrc) fastlane ignores the password inputed when asked on the terminal. Environment fastlane version (run fastlane -v): 1.105.2 Do you use bundler to execute fastlane (i.e. bundle exec fastlane)? Yes Do you use a Ruby environment manager (e.g. chruby  rbenv  rvm)? chruby What Xcode version do you use (e.g. 7.3  8.0) 8.0 Worth noting that this isn't the first time I've experienced this; just that being the numbnuts i am i never took the time to file an issue about this. Recently I tried on a fresh new machine at work (that I configured using my dotfiles repo which carried away the FASTLANE_PASSWORD var) and then I was faced again with a case of ?your password is wrong? even though fastlanewas asking me to input it via terminal and I was copy/pasting it from LastPass. When I was about to rage quit I realised that the variable was set and after removing it and fastlane asking me for the password again  adding the same one I used multiple times (without success) worked. Hope this is enough info to repro; if not let me know and I'll be more than happy to provide more details. PS. Thanks for the amazing work so far

Issue 6648 : iTC now using "no" for Norwegian ， Issue #6648 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description We added Norwegian as app store description on iTunes Connect and downloaded the metadata. A folder no was created. However  in Xcode nn is used for Norwegian. no is an unsupported language code. So the problem is this: if you put no in the Snapfile my iOS 10 simulator runs in English  producing Englisch screenshots in the Screenshots/no folder. Thus the wrong language is uploaded. if you put nn in the Snapfile  the simulator produces Norwegian screenshots  but they end up in an Screenshots/nn folder. Since deliver is looking for the Norwegian screenshots in the wrong folder nothing is being uploaded. I suggest that for uploading no screenshots you also accept files residing in the nn folder.

Issue 6818 : Pilot : submit for external review crashes when it's currently in review or already approved ， Issue #6818 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub I'm using Pilot::BuildManager.new.distribute(config) directly in my Fastfile. Not sure if this is bad practice but it was my best way to reuse code from Pilot and not re-implement everything myself using spaceship. There's a problem with how pilot is handling the submit for external review part. Here is the current timeline of events : Submit a beta for a new build train. The call for client.submit_testflight_build_for_review! is working. However the call build_train.update_testing_status! throws an error "This build could not be used for external testing because the build is not approved." This is a valid error  however it should probably be catched in some way and shown to the user as a warning. The previous beta that was sent to review is either currently in review or approved. The call for client.submit_testflight_build_for_review! is not working and instead a error is thrown "ITC.response.error.INVALID_REQUEST" (can't submit a build to review if it's already in review) The call build_train.update_testing_status! is not called at all since an error is thrown before. Proposed solution : Add attributes in Spaceship::Tunes::Build for betaState and internalState. Current values I've seen are "inactive"  "submitForReview"  "waiting"  "active". I'm missing the in review and approved state. pilot should take into account this value to either not send the build to review  or not send to beta testers if the build is not approved. I can do a pull request. Just wanted to discuss it first.

Issue 8307 : [sigh] Meaningful entitlements like com.apple.developer.associated-domains are removed while resigning ， Issue #8307 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description While resigning an app using sigh resign and --use-app-entitlements flag the logic for blacklisted keys removes some of the important keys  which should be preserved during resigning. See #8295 as an example. Reason The reason is in the order of steps during resigning. Current steps Extract entitlements from provisioning profile Extract entitlements from app binary Merge and patch profile and app entitlements together Remove blacklisted keys from patched entitlements 4.1 This is where the issue occurs - some of the keys that should be preserved are actually removed Resign Suggested steps Extract entitlements from provisioning profile Remove blacklisted keys from profile entitlements Extract entitlements from app binary Merge and patch profile and app entitlements together Resign This way we only apply filter to the provisioning profile entitlements  because this is where unwanted keys may be present. All the keys that were originally part of the app's entitlements are preserved.

Issue 8958 : rubocop violations when using fastlane new_plugin ， Issue #8958 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist [x ] Updated fastlane to the latest version [x ] I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description A new plugin generated using fastlane new_plugin does not pass rubocop without modifying .rubocop.yml. It wants the Fastlane-generated gemspec to be snake case (fastlane_plugin_my_new_action.gemspec). It doesn't like the use of %q{} in the Fastlane-generated action. It wants an empty line after magic comments (# coding: utf-8) I've also seen complaints from the Eval Cop (eval is a security risk) because of the lines added to the Gemfile by fastlane add_plugin  but I didn't reproduce that just now. It's not hard to disable these Cops in .rubocop.yml  but it would be nice if the new_plugin command generated code that passed its own tests. Issue 8978 : xcexport is not working for Xcode 8.3 ， Issue #8978 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description I use xcexport action. xcexport(       export_method: 'ad-hoc'        archive_path: Actions.lane_context[SharedValues::XCODEBUILD_ARCHIVE]        include_bitcode: false     ) But following error is raised. [!] Exit status of command 'set -o pipefail && xcodebuild -archivePath "/Users/device/Library/Developer/Xcode/Archives/2017-04-24/XXXX 2017-04-24 18.08.51.xcarchive" -exportArchive -exportPath "XXXX 2017-04-24 18.08.51" | tee '/Users/device/Library/Logs/fastlane/xcbuild/2017-04-24/57306/xcodebuild.log' | xcpretty --color --simple' was 64 instead of 0. xcodebuild: error: The flag -exportOptionsPlist is required when specifying -exportArchive.  This issue seems to be caused by this changes on Xcode 8.3 The -exportFormat parameter of the -exportArchive option for xcodebuild has been removed. To set the export format  use the -exportOptionsPlist parameter to specify an export plist file with the method key set to the desired format. For more information on the keys and values for the export plist  run xcodebuild -help on the command line  https://developer.apple.com/library/content/releasenotes/DeveloperTools/RN-Xcode/Chapters/Introduction.html

Issue 9094 : Supply and Screengrab can create inconsistent locale directory names in Android metadata ， Issue #9094 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub ? New Issue Checklist Updated fastlane to the latest version I have read the Contribution Guidelines Issue Description I've noticed a discrepancy between the locale directory names that are created after running fastlane supply init and those that are created after running fastlane screengrab. This only occurs with languages that have no country code in the locale name. For example  here are the resulting directory names for each tool for an app with a Google Play listing that supports Arabic  English (GB)  German (DE) and Slovak: Language Supply Directory Name Screengrab Directory Name Arabic ar ar- English (GB) en-GB en-GB German (DE) de-DE de-DE Slovak sk sk- As you can see  the Screengrab directory names for the locales that don't contain a country code still have the dash ("-") appended to the end. This causes problems when updating existing screenshots since the original metadata that Supply created will be contained within the directory without the "-" at the end (e.g. "ar")  and any newly generated screenshots will be automatically placed in the directory with the "-" at the end (e.g. "ar-"). This inconsistency can be manually resolved  but that's not ideal if screenshots are updated with an automated job. It looks like this can be fixed by checking the country code string in the localeToDirName() in screengrab/screengrab-lib/src/main/java/tools.fastlane.screengrab/FileWritingScreenshotCallback.java:107. I'm happy to submit a PR for this fix  but I first wanted to make sure this wasn't intentional behavior  and of course I'd like the feedback of those who are more familiar with the project on whether or not I've diagnosed this issue properly. Issue 9542 : [match] OpenSSL 1.1.0 breaks backwards compatibility with old encrypted keys  etc ， Issue #9542 ， fastlane/fastlane ， GitHub Summary: It looks like OpenSSL 1.1.0 changed something about the default settings they use to encrypt / decrypt files. One possible work-around for this issue would be to modify match to do the following: Try to decrypt the p12 file If that fails  try it again using the older openssl behavior (by appending -md md5 to the openssl command) If that also fails  treat it like an actual failure and continue with the existing (failure) codepath. Details: Here's a stackoverflow post which describes the issue: https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/344586 The default hash used by openssl enc for password-based key derivation changed in 1.1.0 to SHA256 versus MD5 in lower versions. On a box with older openssl installed  match will work correctly. You can test this by manually decrypting one of match's p12 files using this command: openssl aes-256-cbc -k password-goes-here -in ABCDE12345.p12 -out /dev/null -a -d  On a box with openssl 1.1.0+ installed  match will fail: WARN [2017-06-19 16:49:50.76]: Enter the passphrase that should be used to encrypt/decrypt your certificates WARN [2017-06-19 16:49:50.76]: This passphrase is specific per repository and will be stored in your local keychain WARN [2017-06-19 16:49:50.76]: Make sure to remember the password  as you'll need it when you run match on a different machine  [2017-06-19 16:49:50.76]: Passphrase for Git Repo: ********  [2017-06-19 16:49:54.30]: Type passphrase again: ******** bad decrypt 140736683381696:error:06065064:digital envelope routines:EVP_DecryptFinal_ex:bad decrypt:crypto/evp/evp_enc.c:535: ERROR [2017-06-19 16:49:56.67]: Couldn't decrypt the repo  please make sure you enter the right password!  However  if you run the above openssl command and append -md md5 (which forces the old behavior)  it will work  you can correctly decrypt a p12 file which was encrypted using the older version of openssl. The new behavior of openssl is the equivalent of appending -md sha256.
